\&gt;In the B2B sector these contracts are all annualized. Businesses won't  cancel salesforce and square unless they're literally failing, which  is/will happen, but probably not enough to impact short term  valuations....yet...

&amp;#x200B;

Worked in ecommerce software for 4+ years. Beyond being annualized contracts (and, in fact, usually 3 year contracts on auto-renewal) the kinds of implementations that use these tech's are generally boutique hand-built custom things. That's the entire point of Square's API in many ways. Most of the companies which use these tech's are the kinds that do major tech upgrades/replatforming every 10-20 years or so. People who bought into Salesforce in 2008 are probably in the market for smth new, but people who bought into Square will probably stay with their current implementations until at least 2030.
